The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Ballacks apology
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Ballacks apology
                      
	Berlin: Germany coach Joachim Loew won what appeared to be a complete victory in his row with two senior players on Sunday, when Michael Ballack offered an apology and Torsten Frings pledged his future to the team.         
	I will sit down with Joachim Loew as soon as my injury permits and apologise for my behaviour, Ballack said in a statement.         
	Frings, issued a statement of his own saying he would like to carry on playing for Germany.         
	 (REUTERS)                                                                                                                          
